17/03/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia and Montenegro -- Bulgarian Public Works Minister Valentin Tserovski and Serbian Urban Planning Minister Dragoslav Sumarac met on Saturday (15 March) to discuss bilateral co-operation and joint projects aimed at regional development and infrastructure construction.
Sumarac said the project on the Serbian part of the Sofia-Nis highway would be completed within a month.
The two officials agreed to meet again in April to determine the next steps in implementing the joint initiative.
(BTA, Pari, Standart - 17/03/03)
